A: The problem is that you are using PrintWriter.write() which writes the string to the stream but does not add a newline character. This is why you are seeing "123" instead of "1".
If you want to send multiple lines, you should use PrintWriter.println() which writes a line terminated with a line separator.
Here is how you can do it:
PrintWriter printWriter = ...
printWriter.println("1");
printWriter.println("2");
printWriter.println("3");

And to read the lines:
ServerSocket serverSocket = ...
Socket socket = serverSocket.accept();
BufferedReader bufferedReader = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(socket.getInputStream()));
String line;
while ((line = bufferedReader.readLine()) != null) {
    System.out.println(line);
}

This will print each line separately.

